How EVs Don‚Äôt Save You Money
The headline probably has you thinking about the high cost of the EV ‚Äì so high that whatever you ‚Äúsave‚Äù by not buying gas ends up costing you a great deal. But that is only one of the ways EVs don‚Äôt save you money.
Another one is tires.
EV tires wear out faster because EVs are much heavier than other cars ‚Äì because EVs are weighed down by 1,000-plus pounds of batteries. For example, a Tesla Model 3 ‚Äì which is a compact-sized car about the same size as a Honda Civic ‚Äì weighs close to 3,900 pounds (two tons) empty. The Civic weighs just shy of 2,900 pounds ‚Äì a difference of . . . 1,000 pounds.
